        <h1>Designing Services in ALIVE</h1>
      <p>Services in the ALIVE framework must have semantic descriptions; these describe the meaning of the servicesâ€™ inputs, outputs and what they do, in the terms of a broader ontology.&nbsp; At the time of writing, most web services do not yet have these descriptions so you will need to create them. </p>
        <p> There a four primary ways of making new services available in the ALIVE framework, outlined as follows; </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Constructing new web services from source code, using the OWLSBuilder tool</li>
          <li>Adding semantic descriptions to existing web service&nbsp; (WSDL) descriptions using the Service description tool</li>
          <li>Building or re-using service templates which construct new services out of existing ones using the Service Template tool. </li>
      </ul>
    <p>Generating service descriptions from existing coordination tasks.</p>
